{
  "texts": [
    "C. Design of R_advR_ref transfers the optimization scheme that LLM suggests to R_adv, which aims to figure out the specific methods to implement the suggested optimizations on code with the help of LLM.",
    "To achieve this, an intuitive approach is to send the optimization type to LLM after joining it with a prompt like \"how to edit the code to achieve that\".",
    "However, according to our experience, the response from LLM in this way will become unpredictable because of the randomness of LLM.",
    "Thus, we prepare the prompt for each optimization to make the response from LLM is predictable and analyzable.",
    "Moreover, we observe that some optimizations can provide additional information for the other optimizations."
  ]
}